The paper deals with formalising the pi-calculus using nominal logic and implementing it in Isabelle/HOL. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with process calculi and machine checkable proofs, which are topics that fall under Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of induction rules and bisimulation equivalence, which are topics that fall under the Semantics (cs.SE) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the reduction of arguments about bound names, which is a topic that falls under the Logical Frameworks (cs.LF) sub-category.
